quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  33,60,"If the hypocrite and those who have a disease in their hearts and those who spread false rumors in the city do not stop, We shall provoke you against them, then they will only be your neighbors in there for a short while"
  33,61,"They are cursed, and wherever they are found they are taken and they are killed"
  33,62,God’s way about those who passed away in the past. And you never find any change in God’s way
  33,63,"People ask you about the hour, say: its knowledge is only with God. And how would you know, the hour may be near"
  33,64,Indeed God cursed the disbelievers and has prepared a burning fire for them
  33,65,"remaining in there forever and ever, and they do not find any protector or any helper"
  33,66,"In a day that their faces are turned over in the fire, they say: we wish we had obeyed God and obeyed the messenger"
  33,67,"And they say: our Master, we obeyed our leaders and our elders (and great ones), and they misled us from the way"
  33,68,"Our Master, give them double the punishment and curse them, a great curse"
  33,69,"You who believe, do not be like those who harassed Moses, then God cleared him of what they said, and he is respected before God"
  33,70,"You who believe, be cautious of God and say right (and appropriate) word"
  33,71,"so He corrects (and improves) you works for you, and to forgive your sins for you. And whoever obeys God and His messenger then he has achieved a great victory"
  33,72,"Indeed We offered the trust to the skies and the earth and the mountains, but they refused to undertake it and they were afraid of it, but the human being undertook it. Indeed he is wrongdoer and ignorant"
  33,73,"So that God punishes the hypocrite men and the hypocrite women, and the polytheist men and the polytheist women, and He turns (in mercy) to the believing men and the believing women. And God is forgiving and merciful"
  34,1,"All praise belongs to God, the One that whatever in the skies and whatever on the earth belongs to Him, and all praise in the hereafter belongs to Him, and He is the wise and the well informed"
  34,2,"He knows what goes into the earth and what comes out of it, and what comes down from the sky and what goes up to it, and He is the merciful, the forgiving"
  34,3,"And those who disbelieved said: the hour would not come to us. Say: yes, by my Master, knower of the unseen, it shall come to you, a tiny particle in the earth and in the skies does not escape from Him, and neither anything smaller than that or larger, unless it is (written) in a clear book"
  34,4,So that He rewards those who believed and did good works. They have forgiveness and a noble provision
  34,5,"And those who tried to disable (and invalidate) Our signs, they have punishment of a painful filth"
  34,6,"And those who were given the knowledge see that what is revealed to you from your Master is the truth and it guides to the path of the powerful, the praiseworthy"
  34,7,"And those who disbelieved said: should we point you out to a man who tells you that you will certainly be (raised) in a new creation when you are torn into pieces, completely torn apart"
  34,8,"Did he make up a lie (and attributed it) to God or is he mad? No, but those who do not believe in the hereafter are in the punishment and in the extensive (and major) error"
  34,9,"Did they not look at what is in front of them and what is behind them from the sky and the earth? If We want, We would sink them down into the earth or We make a piece of the sky fall on them. Indeed there is a signs in that for every repenting servant"